(41, 16, 16, 66, 20, 15, 15, 'shall be saved', 'Salvation and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of belief and unbelief. Mark 16:16 speaks of salvation for believers, while Revelation 20:15 warns of judgment for those not found in the book of life.', 'theme', 0.685, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 17, 44, 5, 16, 16, 'cast out devils', 'Signs of Believers'' Power', 'Both passages emphasize the power of believers to cast out unclean spirits and heal the sick. Mark 16:17 mentions casting out devils, while Acts 5:16 describes healing those vexed with unclean spirits.', 'theme', 0.5449999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 17, 46, 12, 28, 28, 'speak with new tongues', 'Signs and Gifts in the Church', 'Both passages emphasize the role of ''diversities of tongues'' as a sign of belief and a gift within the church. Mark highlights the ability to ''speak with new tongues,'' while 1 Corinthians lists ''diversities of tongues'' among the spiritual gifts.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 17, 42, 10, 17, 17, 'cast out devils', 'Authority in Jesus'' Name', 'Both passages emphasize the power of Jesus'' name in casting out devils. Mark 16:17 mentions believers casting out devils in His name, while Luke 10:17 shows the seventy disciples experiencing this authority firsthand.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 17, 44, 8, 7, 7, 'cast out devils', 'Signs of Believers'' Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the casting out of unclean spirits and healing as signs that follow believers. Mark 16:17 mentions casting out devils, while Acts 8:7 describes unclean spirits coming out of those possessed, showcasing the fulfillment of this promise.', 'theme', 0.517, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 17, 43, 14, 12, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Belief and Works', 'Both passages emphasize the power of belief in Jesus and the resulting works that believers will perform. Mark 16:17 mentions signs following believers, while John 14:12 states that those who believe will do works like Jesus and even greater ones.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 17, 46, 12, 10, 10, 'speak with new tongues', 'Connection of Spiritual Gifts', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of ''tongues'' as a sign of belief and a spiritual gift. They highlight the role of believers in performing miraculous acts and speaking in new languages.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 17, 41, 9, 38, 38, 'cast out devils', 'Authority in Jesus'' Name', 'This connection highlights the authority given to believers to cast out devils in Jesus'' name, as seen in both passages. Mark 16:17 emphasizes that believers will perform such acts, while Mark 9:38 shows an example of someone doing so, despite not being part of the inner circle.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 18, 42, 10, 19, 19, 'take up serpents', 'Power Over Harmful Creatures', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to believers over dangerous creatures and harmful substances. They highlight the assurance that nothing will harm them as they exercise this power.', 'theme', 0.6639999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 18, 59, 5, 14, 15, 'lay hands on the sick', 'Healing and Faith Connection', 'Both passages emphasize healing through faith and prayer. Mark 16:18 mentions laying hands on the sick, while James 5:14-15 discusses prayer and anointing for healing.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 18, 44, 28, 3, 6, 'if they drink any deadly thing, it shall not hurt them', 'Connection of Divine Protection', 'Both passages emphasize protection from harm. Mark 16:18 states that believers will not be harmed by deadly things, while Acts 28:3-6 illustrates Paul''s experience with a viper, where he felt no harm after being bitten.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 18, 44, 19, 12, 12, 'lay hands on the sick', 'Healing and Deliverance Connections', 'Both passages emphasize healing and deliverance from sickness. Mark 16:18 mentions laying hands on the sick, while Acts 19:12 describes handkerchiefs bringing healing to the sick.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 18, 19, 91, 13, 13, 'take up serpents', 'Connection of Serpents and Safety', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine protection against dangerous creatures. Both passages emphasize the ability to overcome threats, such as serpents and lions, through faith.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 18, 41, 5, 23, 23, 'lay hands on the sick', 'Healing Through Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of laying hands as a means of healing. In Mark 16:18, it states they shall lay hands on the sick, while Mark 5:23 describes a plea for Jesus to lay hands on a dying daughter for her healing.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 18, 45, 16, 20, 20, NULL, 'Divine Protection and Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine protection over believers. Both passages emphasize God''s power to safeguard and deliver His followers from harm, as seen in the promise of safety in Mark and the assurance of victory over evil in Romans.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 19, 60, 3, 22, 22, 'sat on the right hand of God', 'Ascension and Authority Connection', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus being ''on the right hand of God,'' highlighting his exaltation and authority after his ascension into heaven. This connection illustrates the continuity of Jesus'' position of power in both texts.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 19, 58, 1, 3, 3, 'sat on the right hand of God', 'Seated at God''s Right Hand', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus being ''sat down on the right hand of God'' after His ascension. This connection highlights the significance of His position of authority and glory in heaven.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 19, 58, 12, 2, 2, 'sat on the right hand of God', 'Jesus'' Position at God''s Right Hand', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' exaltation after His resurrection. Both passages emphasize that Jesus is ''set down at the right hand of God,'' signifying His authority and completion of His work.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 19, 19, 110, 1, 1, 'sat on the right hand of God', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of sitting at the right hand of God, signifying authority and power. Mark 16:19 describes Jesus being received into heaven and sitting at God''s right hand, while Psalms 110:1 speaks of the Lord commanding another to sit at His right hand.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 19, 45, 8, 34, 34, 'sat on the right hand of God', 'Christ at the Right Hand', 'Both passages emphasize Christ''s position at the right hand of God, highlighting His authority and role in intercession. This connection underscores the continuity of Christ''s exaltation after His resurrection.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 19, 44, 2, 33, 33, 'sat on the right hand of God', 'Exaltation at God''s Right Hand', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus'' exaltation, as both passages mention Him being ''at the right hand of God.'' Mark 16:19 describes Jesus'' ascension, while Acts 2:33 emphasizes His exalted position and the outpouring of the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 19, 44, 7, 55, 56, 'right hand of God', 'Connection of Jesus'' Position', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' position at the right hand of God. Mark 16:19 states he sat at God''s right hand, while Acts 7:55-56 describes him standing there, highlighting his exalted status.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 20, 46, 2, 4, 5, 'the Lord working with them', 'Demonstration of God''s Power', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s power in both passages. Mark 16:20 speaks of the Lord confirming the word with signs, while 1 Corinthians 2:4-5 emphasizes the demonstration of the Spirit and of power.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 20, 44, 14, 3, 3, 'the Lord working with them', 'Signs and Wonders Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the Lord''s role in confirming the message through signs. Mark highlights the Lord working with them, while Acts mentions the Lord granting signs and wonders.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 20, 44, 8, 4, 6, 'preached every where', 'Preaching and Miracles Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of preaching and the accompanying miracles. In Mark, the Lord confirms the word with signs, while in Acts, Philip''s preaching is followed by miracles that draw the people''s attention.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 20, 45, 15, 19, 19, 'signs following', 'Signs and Wonders in Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the role of signs and wonders in confirming the preaching of the gospel. Mark 16:20 mentions the Lord working with them and confirming the word with signs, while Romans 15:19 highlights the power of the Spirit of God through mighty signs and wonders.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 20, 58, 2, 4, 4, 'signs following', 'Signs and Wonders Connection', 'Both passages emphasize God''s confirmation of the message through signs and wonders. This connection highlights the divine endorsement of the apostles'' preaching and the witness of God through miracles.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 16, 20, 46, 3, 6, 9, 'the Lord working with them', 'God''s Role in Growth', 'Both passages emphasize the active role of God in the ministry. In Mark, the Lord confirms the word with signs, while in Corinthians, it is God who gives the increase, highlighting divine involvement in the work of believers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
